newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soybeans, meal turn firm on wheat rally.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soybeans, meal turn firm on wheat rally.

text.p: CBOT soybean and soymeal futures turned firm as wheat continued to rally and Refco Inc bought soybeans, traders said.
Refco had been a seller in early dealings, traders said.
Wheat prices continued to trade seven to nine cents per bushel higher after USDA lowered wheat ending stocks and world wheat supply projections in Tuesday's crop report.

USDA raised its estimate for U.S. soybean production to 2.403 billion bushels, above trade expectations. But traders also noted demand figures were strong as USDA raised its projections for Chinese imports.
At 1221 CDT, soybeans were four to 1/2 cents higher, with November up four cents at $6.84 a bushel. Soymeal was $4.30 higher to $1.00 lower, with December up $4.30 at $231.00 a ton.
